overview: The user wanted to transform their sleep questionnaire app's
  aesthetics from a generic look to a more beautiful and professional design. I
  began by analyzing the existing styling, identifying areas like the color
  palette, layout, and form elements that needed refinement. I then implemented
  a new sleep-themed color palette, redesigned the main form layout with subtle
  background effects and an improved progress indicator, and polished various UI
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders. The welcome screen was
  enhanced with a hero section and feature cards, and consistent styling was
  applied across all questionnaire sections. During the process, a console error
  related to null input values was identified and fixed by modifying the Input
  component to safely handle such values. Finally, a second review led to
  further refinements, including replacing hardcoded alert colors with
  theme-based utility classes and increasing border opacities for better visual
  definition. The outcome is a visually cohesive, calming, and professional
  sleep health application.
